snippet.textDisplay:
Pakistani music has always been bold and brave, same goes for Rohail's Coke studio. It complied with the idea of experimentation which in itself is brave and it is understandable to fail in experiments. But now they have become people pleasers and the whole concept of "Sound of Nation" has long gone and gone is the folk and regional influences, gone is the originality. What is left of Coke studio is flashy costumes and "Big" starcast with little to no attempt of experiment. Its really heartbreaking to see immensely talented musicians and singers performing in "safe" boundaries. If the artists are not given the freedom to create then they won't ever pour their hearts out, then you'll only have mediocrity which isn't what Coke studio is all about.
Trying to play safe and still failing at it. What a disgrace!!

P.S. I only like Salman's Solo
